# What I Learnt From This Task

* CSV + AI = instant dashboards: Learned to upload vehicle CSV data into Claude and generate a full HTML dashboard with zero code.

* Data visualization on autopilot: Claude built KPI cards, SVG gauges, fuel comparison charts, and maintenance cost breakdowns from raw data.

* Fuel economics analysis: Got E85 vs Petrol break-even calculations, cost-per-km, and environmental impact metrics auto-calculated.

* One prompt, full app: The Vehicle Cost Analysis prompt turned CSV rows into an interactive HTML file I can open in any browser.

* Actionable insights: Dashboard highlighted total ownership cost, fuel efficiency trends, and where I’m overspending on maintenance.

# Tools Used

* Claude AI - Vehicle Cost Analysis Dashboard prompt, HTML + SVG generation

* CSV dataset - Vehicle data from Google Drive for fuel, maintenance, mileage

* Browser - Open and test generated HTML dashboard locally

* Git + GitHub - Day17 folder, day17.md, HTML file, screenshots, commit & push

* Screenshot tool - Capture KPI cards, charts, gauges, break-even analysis.
